cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CR

The paper focuses on measuring network traffic generated by P2P IPTV applications during the FIFA world cup, analyzing traffic statistics and churn of peers within these P2P networks, and inferring the mechanisms of such applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with multimedia streaming, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper analyzes the behavior of users, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the impact of P2P IPTV on the network, which could be related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
